author: John Wildermuth
title: Prop. F would require business license, but author doesn’t have one
text:
Photo: Brant Ward / Brant Ward / The Chronicle PR executive Dale Carlson walks through City Hall to a meeting with supervisors Monday April 28, 2014 about a group of neighborhood activists who were organizing a ballot initiative to rein in short-term rentals like Airbnb in San Francisco, Calif. PR executive Dale Carlson walks through City Hall to a meeting with...
Dale Carlson, an author of Proposition F, a November ballot initiative that would require more city paperwork for short-term rental units, has never had a San Francisco business license, despite running his public relations company in the city since at least 2007, he admitted Wednesday.
